Preheat your oven to 200°C and boil a large #saucepan{} of water over high heat. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the @Skin-On British Chicken Breasts{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once the oil is hot, lay in the chicken breasts skin-side down. Fry until the skin is golden, ~{5-6%minutes}, then turn and cook for ~{1%minute} on the other side.

> For the crispiest skin, don't be tempted to move the chicken.

> Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging.

While the chicken cooks, trim the @Carrot{3} (no need to peel), quarter lengthways and then chop into batons the length of your index finger. Pop them onto a large #baking tray{} and add a drizzle of @oil{}. Sprinkle over the @Sugar{1%suitable amount} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then arrange in a single layer.

Transfer the chicken to another #baking tray{} (skin-side up). Roast the chicken on the top shelf of your oven and the carrots on the middle shelf, until the carrots are tender and the chicken cooked, ~{20-25%minutes}. Halfway through, add the @Garlic Clove{2}(whole, no need to peel) to the carrot tray to cook for ~{10%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, chop the @Potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop them into your pan of boiling water with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Simmer until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop them back in their pan. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm. Meanwhile, thinly slice the @Closed Cup Mushrooms{150%g}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Echalion Shallot{1}.

Put the frying pan you cooked your chicken in back on medium-high heat (no need to wash). Add a drizzle of @oil{}, the mushrooms, @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%g} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until the mushrooms are golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

> Cook lardons thoroughly.

Add the shallot and fry until soft, about ~{3%minutes}. Pour in the @Water{125%ml} and add the @Red Wine Stock Paste{14%g}. Stir to combine, then simmer until the sauce has thickened slightly and is glossy, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

When the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a #chopping board{} to rest for a couple of mins. Carefully, squeeze the garlic out of its skin and add it to the potato along with a knob of @butter{1%knob} and a splash of @?milk{} (if you have some). Add @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Slice the chicken, serve with the mash and carrots. Spoon over the sauce. Enjoy!

> If you've decided to add bacon lardons to your meal, add them to the pan with the mushrooms. Continue with the rest of the recipe as instructed.